* Comparar con las tecnolog√≠as modernas (Node.js y Django).

---

### üîê Autenticaci√≥n (.htaccess)

```bash
sudo apt install apache2-utils -y
sudo htpasswd -c /etc/apache2/.htpasswd alumno1
sudo nano /var/www/html/privado/.htaccess
```

Contenido:

```
AuthType Basic
AuthName "Zona restringida"
AuthUserFile /etc/apache2/.htpasswd
Require valid-user
```

---

### üíª Activaci√≥n de PHP

```bash
sudo apt install -y php libapache2-mod-php
echo "<?php phpinfo(); ?>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/info.php
sudo systemctl reload apache2
```

---

### ‚òï Tomcat Manager

```bash
sudo apt install -y tomcat10 tomcat10-admin
sudo nano /etc/tomcat10/tomcat-users.xml
```

Agregar:

```xml
<role rolename="manager-gui"/>
<user username="admin" password="admin123" roles="manager-gui"/>
```

Reiniciar:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart tomcat10
```

Acceso en navegador:
üëâ [http://localhost:8080/manager/html](http://localhost:8080/manager/html)

### üß∞ Comandos de repaso

```bash
# Apache
sudo apt install apache2 -y
sudo a2enmod rewrite proxy proxy_http
sudo systemctl reload apache2

# PHP
sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php -y

# Tomcat
sudo apt install tomcat10 tomcat10-admin -y
sudo systemctl restart tomcat10

# Proxy Apache ‚Üí Tomcat
ProxyPass "/app" "http://localhost:8080/hola/"
ProxyPassReverse "/app" "http://localhost:8080/hola/"
```

---

